  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 23:30 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] JTO scorer adds decay guard, paper-only\n\n**Task:** Add/verify a JTO-specific scorer that reports 15m/30m separately, flags 60m decay, and keeps live gating disabled until deduped n >= 20 with post-fee/slippage edge.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- Updated `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/score_hl_jto_momentum.py`.\n- Added explicit output fields: `decay_60m`, `recommended_horizons`, `live_ready`, and `live_block_reason`.\n- Live readiness now requires deduped 15m sample **n >= 20**, positive 15m/30m average return, 15m/30m WR **>=55%**, and no 60m decay.\n- Ran the scorer after patch: HL paper rows **107**, JTO STRONG_TREND deduped rows **4**, all `pass_filter`.\n- Vol buckets: `1.5-2.0x` **3**, `>=2.0x` **1**.\n- Returns: 15m **4 rows / 100.0% WR / +0.006374 avg / +0.005997 median**; 30m **4 rows / 75.0% WR / +0.003699 avg / +0.008803 median**; 60m **4 rows / 25.0% WR / -0.004983 avg / -0.008065 median**.\n- Guard output: `decay_60m=True`, `recommended_horizons=[\"15m\",\"30m\"]`, `live_ready=False`, block reason `paper_only: require deduped n>=20, positive 15m/30m edge, >=55% WR, and no 60m decay`.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-jto-scorer-adds-decay-guard-paper-only-2026-05-03-2330.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The JTO branch still has the best P3 signal quality, but the decay guard is doing exactly what it should: it prevents accidental live-readiness while 60m reverses hard and sample size is tiny. The interesting edge is short-horizon momentum only, not a broad JTO long or generic volatility branch.\n\n**Decision:** Keep JTO STRONG_TREND paper-only. Use 15m/30m as the only recommended research horizons. Treat 60m as decay/reversal risk. Do not enable live gating until deduped n >= 20 and post-fee/slippage edge survives. Keep generic vol, RANGE-vol, and MIXED branches disabled/paper-only. Keep HL live notional-blocked.\n\n**Next:** Monitor new JTO STRONG_TREND candidates and compare `1.5-2.0x` versus `>=2.0x` vol buckets once n grows. If 60m decay persists, hard-code future JTO exit research around <=30m horizons only.\n\n## 2026-05-03 23:24 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Sunday 23:00 chop to negative in-band under max P1 risk-off\n\n**Task:** Re-check PM smart-entry tape after P1 escalated BTC to maximum hard defensive and P4 stayed trend-risk-off/chop, focusing on whether PM tape gives any reason to loosen weekend/price filters.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- `confidence_outcomes.jsonl` remains unchanged: rows **201**, latest outcome **2026-04-07T19:35:15.678249+00:00**, alpha-tagged rows **0**.\n- Re-ran `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/analyze_20utc_alpha_outcomes.py`: rows **201**, alpha-tagged **0**, 20 UTC alpha-tagged **0**, status **DATA_GAP**.\n- PM no-trade rows since 23:00 UTC: **20**, all **WEEKEND_FILTER**.\n- Bias",
